Given an array of integers A, print all the peak elements in it 
Note: An array element is peak if it is NOT smaller than its neighbors.

For corner elements, we need to consider only one neighbor.
For example, for input array {5, 10, 20, 15}, 20 is the only peak element.
For example, for input array {5, 20, 10, 15, 5}, 20 and 15 are peak elements.


